{"lemma":"فُرْسِ","slug":"فُرْسِ","root":"ف.ر.س","root_slug":"ف-ر-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33494","n33495"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a Persian"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Persian"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the Persian language"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nOld Persian 𐎱𐎠𐎼𐎿 (p-a-r-s /⁠pārs⁠/)\nMiddle Persian pʾls (/⁠pārs⁠/)\nMiddle Persian -yk' (/⁠-īg⁠/)\nMiddle Persian pʾlsyk' (/⁠pārsīg⁠/)\nEarly New Persian پَارْسِی (pārsī)bor.\nArabic فارسي\nBorrowed from Early New Persian پَارْسِی (pārsī).\n\nShortened form of اللِّسَانُ الْفَارِسِيّ (al-lisānu l-fārisiyy)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33494","headword_ar":"فِرْسٌ","root":"frs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, S, M, O, K:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSoqaAS","text_ar":"قَصْقَاص"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, and so in copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaDoqaAD","text_ar":"قَضْقَاض"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the CK,) [each said to be a name of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^u$onaAn","text_ar":"اُشْنَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kali"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Syria,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,] accord. to Abu-l-Meká- rim: (O:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habon","text_ar":"حَبْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"barowaq","text_ar":"بَرْوَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (O, K:) or the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small kind of thorny trees called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iros","text_ar":"شِرْس"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n33495","headword_ar":"فَرَسٌ","root":"frs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mare;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of what are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayolN","text_ar":"خَيْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) the name"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frs","text_ar":"فرس"},{"kind":"text","text":"is given to it because it crushes and breaks the ground with its hoofs; (A, O; *) and is applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) but mostly applied to the latter; (M;) the female not being called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasapN","text_ar":"فَرَسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O;) or the female is [sometimes] thus called: (Yoo, IJ, M, Msb, K:) it is applied also to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arabian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) and to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turkish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or that which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not Arabian:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or, accord. to Mohammad [the Hanafee Imám], to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Arabian only;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but for this [says Mtr] I find no authority of a lexicologist, except that ISk, speaking of a solid-hoofed animal, says, “ whether it be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"birozawon","text_ar":"بِرْزَوْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faras","text_ar":"فَرَس"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagol","text_ar":"بَغْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaAr","text_ar":"حِمَار"},{"kind":"text","text":": ” (Mgh:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaAsN","text_ar":"اَفْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) [a pl. of pauc. but used as a pl. of mult. also,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforusN","text_ar":"اَفْرُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [a pl. of pauc. only,] (O,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwsN","text_ar":"فُرُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally fem., you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvu A^aforaAsK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثُ اَفْرَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when you mean males [as well as when you mean females]: (M:) or you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvapu A^aforaAsK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثَةُ اَفْرَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", when you mean males; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"valaAvu A^aforaAsK","text_ar":"ثَلَاثُ اَفْرَاسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", when you mean females: (Msb:) the dim. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furayosN","text_ar":"فُرَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,) when applied to the male; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furayosapN","text_ar":"فُرَيْسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", when applied to the female; (S, O, Msb;) agreeably with rule; (Msb;) accord. to Aboo-Bekr Ibn-Es-Sarráj: (S, O:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furayosN","text_ar":"فُرَيْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"when applied to the female [also], which is extr. (Sb, M. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA kafarasaYo rihaAnK","text_ar":"هُمَا كَفَرَسَىْ رِهَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They two are like two horses running for a wager"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a saying applied to two persons running a race to a goal, and being equal: (A, O, K:) the comparison relating to the beginning [of a contest], for the termination necessarily shows which outstrips; (O, K:) and to two who are equal, and two who are nearly equal, in excellence &c. (Har p. 640.) It was said by a man who swore that he would abstain from his wife for four months, and then divorced her: for the period during which a woman may be taken back after a [first or second] divorce is that of three menstruations or three periods of purity from menstruation; and if it ended in this case before the end of the four months during which he swore to abstain from her, she became separated from him by that divorcement: so he likened the two periods to two horses running for a wager. (O, * TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasu AlbaHori","text_ar":"فَرَسُ البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The horse of the great river;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., of the Nile;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hippopotamus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Dmr. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasu","text_ar":"الفَرَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known constellation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because of its resemblance in form to a horse; (M;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasu AlA^aEoZamu","text_ar":"الفَرَسُ الاَعْظَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Greater,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Greatest, Horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the constellation Pegasus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiToEapu Alfarasi","text_ar":"قِطْعَةُ الفَرَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Piece of the Horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the constellation Equuleus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasu Alt~aAm~u","text_ar":"الفَرَسُ التَّامُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Complete horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain constellation composed of thirty-one stars, in which a portion of the constellation called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasu AlA^aEoZamu","text_ar":"الفَرَسُ الاَعْظَمُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is included."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw. [It is further described by him; but in a manner that does not enable me to identify it with any of the constellations named by our astronomers.])"}],"source_refs":["Yoo","IJ","M","Msb","K","Mgh","S","O","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}